Pre-Game Insights: The Republic of Ireland squad was training at the Olympic Stadium, Helsinki, Finland, on Wednesday.
The match is described as a relegation showdown with Finland.
Ireland fans have been contemplating whether relegation might be beneficial due to the possibility of facing weaker opposition.
Ireland has lost the last eight serious games in a row, excluding two wins against Gibraltar, marking their worst run in recent memory.
Heimir Hallgrímsson, the coach, described the situation not as a 'losing streak' but a 'downward spiral'.
